      <guid>http://localhost:1313/en/bitcoin-is-the-mycelium/</guid>
      <description>&lt;blockquote class=&#34;book-hint btc&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;p&gt;This series by Brandon Quittem was published in his &lt;a href=&#34;https://brandonquittem.com/bitcoin-is-the-mycelium-of-money&#34;&gt;blog&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/contribute/&#34;&gt;Contribute&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;foreward&#34;&gt;&#xA;  Foreward&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#foreward&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;I need to give credit to Dan Held for publishing his 4-part series &lt;a href=&#34;https://medium.com/@danhedl/planting-bitcoin-sound-money-72e80e40ff62&#34;&gt;comparing bitcoin’s origin to planting a tree&lt;/a&gt;. While I loved his series, I believe a more robust analogy is comparing bitcoin to fungi. If you’re new to this topic, strap in — it is my honor to initiate you into the fascinating world of fungi.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
